g.text: Backtracking (Algorithm) :- Create a branch of sub problem and check for dead end,
if dead end occur, then go back to pervious stage via backtracking.
Example : 3,1,2 :- Find ascending order of given number.
N Queen problem :- Place 4 queen in 4 X 4 matrix, such that no queen can attack.
i) if current coordinate, have row or column same as existing queens placed.
iii) if subtraction of current point and existing queen placed row and column same, then current point is diagonally left clashed.
ii) if addition of current point and existing queen placed row and column same, then current point is diagonally right clashed
